      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="about-bio">
        <p>I'm an eLearning developer based in Bangalore with a decade of experience building scalable, accessible digital learning solutions for global organisations.</p>
        <p>My core stack spans the full eLearning delivery chain — from authoring standards like <strong>SCORM 1.2 / 2004</strong> and <strong>xAPI (Tin Can)</strong> to open-source frameworks including the <strong>Adapt Framework</strong> for responsive HTML5 courseware and <strong>Sunbird</strong> for large-scale learning platforms. I work closely with LMS administrators and instructional designers to make sure content doesn't just launch — it tracks, reports, and improves.</p>
        <p>Beyond standards and frameworks, I enjoy the intersection of JavaScript engineering and learning design — writing custom Adapt plugins, configuring xAPI statement templates, or wiring up a Sunbird instance for a government skilling programme.</p>
        <p>This blog is where I document the things I figure out along the way: server setups, LMS quirks, tooling experiments, and the occasional deep dive into accessibility in courseware.</p>

        <h3 class="about-section-title">Focus areas</h3>
